            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@trusktr This is totally incorrect, the only right way to set this environment variable is using terminal emulator’s own settings (like `set-option -g default-terminal …` in tmux or “environment variables” list in profile in konsole). Otherwise you will sooner or later run into situation where termcap returns sequences that have nothing to do with your terminal emulator. Not to mention the fact that Neovim is not the only application which needs to access termcap and thus receive correct `$TERM`.",
            "created_at": "2017-06-20T04:40:48Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/2334#issuecomment-309642961",
